Position: Junior Web Developer 
Location: Providence, RI 02908
Job Type: Contract
Duration: 1 year, 9/7/2020 – 9/7/2021

JOB DESCRIPTION 
As a member of the ETSS Web Services Team, the Jr. Web Developer will be involved in the design, development, and maintenance of new and existing state government websites and applications. 
SUPERVISION RECEIVED: 
Works under the general supervision of the ETSS Web Development Manager with considerable latitude for the exercise of independent judgment in website design and development and the application of website content maintenance techniques; work is reviewed upon completion for results achieved and conformance to agency policies and objectives. 
ILLUSTRATIVE EXAMPLES OF WORK PERFORMED: 

Provide technical value to the Web Services team in the design and development of government websites and web applications;
Prioritize and address assigned agency service requests in a timely manner and ensure quality and integrity of web design, development, and content solutions;
To conceptualize and design websites and other informational material utilizing a variety of page layout software to set size specifications, computer typesetting, typography, pagination and other graphic elements ensuring adherence to deadlines and budget requirements;
To ensure all web design and development activities conform to web standards and state policies; 
To coordinate design details, assignments and projects by collaborating with staff members and management to meet specified deadlines;
To serve as a resource in one or more highly specialized areas of web applications development, systems analysis, and programming;
To prepare and maintain documentation of all web design and development projects in progress and completed;
Other duties as assigned.

EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS 
Minimum Required Experience: 

Demonstrated experience in the design, development, and implementation of small to mid-scale websites; 
Demonstrated web development experience working on a government project (federal, state, or local level);
A thorough knowledge of internet technologies, open source scripting languages, or other web-based technology; 
Proven track record of successful completion of web design / development work – ensuring adherence to project scope, schedule and budget. 

Required Skills: 

Strong working knowledge of web design and development best-practices; 
A thorough knowledge and proficiency with Adobe Creative Cloud products, especially Photoshop, InDesign, Illustrator, and Dreamweaver;
Working knowledge of LAMP web service stack and strong PHP / MySQL programming skills;
Strong communications skills including the ability to build relationships and effectively communicate with all key stakeholders; 
Excellent writing skills; 
Flexible team player with strong organizational skills; 
Ability to establish and achieve goals and meet aggressive timelines; 

Desired: 

Exhibit proficiency in the design, development, and implementation of any well-known responsive front-end frameworks and / or Content Management Systems; 
Deep understanding of website architectures, content management / auditing best practices, and the delivery of omnichannel content; 
Understanding of UX/UI concepts and best practices; 
Familiarity with web technologies such as HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, JQuery, Python, XML, and JSON; 
Knowledge of Search Engine Optimization (SEO) best practices and analytics; 
Working knowledge of ADA and Section 508 Accessibility guidelines; 
Knowledge of building and consuming SOAP and/or RESTful web services; 
Knowledge of all major social media platforms and the processes for seamlessly integrating these technologies into any website framework. 

EDUCATION AND EXPERIENCE: 
Education: 

Such as may have been gained through graduation from a college of recognized standing with at least a Bachelor’ s Degree in Communications/Journalism, Information Systems, Computerized Graphic Design, or a closely related field

Experience: 

Such as may have been gained through: a minimum of two years’ experience as a software engineer or analyst, web design / development specialist, programmer or programmer analyst.\xa0 
Experience as a digital content manager involving the dissemination and daily maintenance of materials involving the use of web content management software in the presentation of web pages, graphics, informational materials and/or publications. 
Or, any combination of education and experience that shall be substantially equivalent to the above education and experience.

\xa0

Recommended skills
Web Development
Html5
Lamp (Software Bundle)
Php (Scripting Language)
J Query
Content Management

